text: Are the Browns better, possibly, or are the Steelers just one of what looks to be a lot of mediocre teams to start the NFL season?
Where did the Bears passing game go?
Now is when we'll find out if Maddon made the right move by taking out Lester...its only the right move if the Cubs bullpen gets through the 8th without allowing a run...
Poor J.R.

(2 of 2) It's absent the glut of analytics and metrics, and dives deep into the human drama of the relationship between two men at the core of one of the great ensembles in American sports history... https://t.co/DNGnTL94bY

Cubs meltdown is nearly complete...can't hold a 6-1 lead at home against the going-nowhere Pirates in a must-win game for division purposes. Qualifying for the playoffs has never been a bad consolation prize for the Cubbies...perhaps until now.
Trying to NOT blame Trubiski for that 11-point swing but hard not to...the really dumb interception cost at least a Bears FG and ball to Miami...hope it's a lesson he learns once!
And where is the alleged upgrade in receivers and all the imaginative passing game that was promised all summer?
Simply cannot imagine a U.S. Open final match evolving in such a dramatic controversial way. Has a chair umpire ever been such a villain?
So now we HAVE to wonder whether that changed charge/block call involving Durant and LeBron took Game 1 from the Cavaliers?
Looks like somebody has discovered how to beat a suddenly lazy Bears defense which cant dial up any pressure or tackle worth a darn...
This is  too great a Game 1 to see the Cavs just sort of implode like this at the end...
The number of empty seats at a Redskins home game in September is astonishing...
So...Nagy went straight George Halas the entire 4th quarter...what's he got now?
Hard to believe the Warriors are essentially dead even in this game with Curry being 1-for-14...
Now let's see what this new Bears offense really has...
Trying to decide whether as a Bears fan all my life whether I should be encouraged at the overall improvement or angry at yet another choke job vs the Packers.
Do I dare say again that it's time to see what Nagy and Trubisky and this new offense are made of?
has there been a more pathetic looking 37-yard FG ever?
2 1/2 minutes in Lambeau for Aaron Rodgers, down 6? Its either him or Brady you want in this situation the last 10 years...
Ooops on me...missed FT
The Carl Edwards Jr fascination needs to end...Yesterday.
Like a great many of us Green and JR Smith had already counted that missed GT as good...and a CLE 1 point lead...Ooops

Trubiski, despite an enormous mistake that led to an 11-point swing, was much more up to the moment than his head coach whose reputation for being daring on offense apparently doesnt convey late in games against good teams.
Why, on fourth-and-five in OT, would the Browns throw THAT pass? Pure stupidity. And how do the officials not call illegal contact on the Ravens defense? Awful officiating?
LeBron James is an amazing dude...but he and his Cavs mates are looking a little tired for the first time tonight now that the pace is up...
If only Ryan Pace had the foresight to trade up in the draft and get a QB like Trubiski...
What top level coach in the NFL wouldnt trust his franchise QB to go win the game with it clearly within reach by throwing a pass on 3rd-and-manageable? Hugely disappointing loss...
For that matter, Great quarter for Trubiski. He doesnt have to be prolific for the Bears, with this defense, to win. Efficient will be more than enough...
If your interest in Sawx-Yanks is waning flip over to Basketball: A Love Story...its riveting for anybody who considers himself a basketball fan...the Wilt-Russell stuff should be mandatory...
More nervous watching this game than the night before my son was born!!! #JUSTONERUNCUBBIES!

Three HUGE games all at Wrigley in four days...one run in a 2-1 loss to the Cardinals, one run in a 3-1 loss to the Brewers for the division title and home field advantage, one loss in a do-or-die playoff game to the Rockies...3 runs in four games. unbelievable...
you wonder if morale has to be reconstructed after watching two different teams celebrate on YOUR home field in back-to-back days.
How can you take the Colts seriously when four or five of 'em, down 14 points, run to one end of the field to mug for some picture?
Collinsworth line: "This could set the Bears back 100 years" is sadly in play. Defense keeps it close, offense stinks late. Nothing new there.

Freeland was A-plus for the Rockies tonight...but Cubs hitters are making everybody look like Koufax the last month or so...1 run or none this many times with that many much talent in the lineup cannot happen.
Jeff Van Gundy is right...this game should be called now.

2 losses this season for the Bears: pin both on the head coach...he either didn't have confidence in competing one pass to set up a reasonable FG attempt today or was just not up to the moment as a playcaller...
Those 2nd and 3rd down calls from Nagy were inexcusable...he was afraid late in Green Bay as a play caller and afraid in Miami as a play caller. How disappointing! That's innovative football?
Once again, let's see what Nagy and and Trubisky and this offense are made of. Sitting on a lead in Lambeau ain't gonna get it...not even if #12 is limping around on one leg...
Tell me that's not a Butt Fumble!!!
